					<msContents class="#STM">
						<summary><p>Transcriptions of Tamil and Sanskrit inscriptions mostly by Ariel. Contains also translations, descriptions of temples, maps, drawings, <foreign xml:lang="sa">yantra</foreign>s, syllabaries. Various papers of various format bound, seemingly partly in disorder, in one volume.</p>
<p>The volume contains:
  <list rend="numbered">
    <item><locus facs="0">f1</locus>: map/plan.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f2-f3</locus>: missing folios, if ever existed.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f4-f9</locus>: transcription of inscriptions in Tamil script (versos blank).</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f10</locus>: transcription of an inscription in Tamil script.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f11-f13</locus>: description in French of the temple at Tiruvakkarai.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f14-f15</locus>: temple map (Tiruvakkarai?).</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f16-f18</locus>: transcription of inscriptions (original script in the left column; standardised version in modern Tamil script in the right column).</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f19-f33</locus>: copy of  appendix of Ellis’ <title xml:lang="en">Mirasi Rights</title> (see <locus facs="0">f33v</locus>).</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f34-f36</locus>: wall drawings with inscriptions transcribed in Tamil at their location on the wall.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f37</locus>: transcription of an inscription in Tamil script.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f38</locus>: TBC.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f39-f43</locus>: transcription of inscriptions in Tamil script.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f44</locus>: TBC.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f45</locus>: transcription of inscriptions (original script in the left column; standardised version in modern Tamil script in the right column).</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f46</locus>: TBC.</item>
        <item><locus facs="0">f47</locus>: TBC.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f48</locus>: title page <quote xml:lang="fr">Inscriptions tamiles. 1ère section Bahour 1852. 1 à <space type="vacat"/></quote>.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f49-f71</locus>: transcription of inscriptions from Pākūr (Bahour) (original script in the left column; standardised version in modern Tamil script in the right column).</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f72</locus>: title page <quote xml:lang="fr">copies originales d'inscriptions à Bahour</quote>.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f73-f82</locus>: transcription of inscriptions from Pākūr in Tamil script .</item>
        <item><locus facs="0">f83</locus>: title page <quote xml:lang="fr"><term xml:lang="ta">Tiruvakkarai</term> 12 au 1? Août 52</quote>.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f84-f108</locus>: transcription of inscriptions from Tiruvakkarai (original script in the left column; standardised version in modern Tamil script in the right column, as it happens [not always completed]).</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f109-f111</locus>: translations into French.</item>
<item><locus facs="0">f112</locus>: title page <quote xml:lang="fr"> Diverses inscriptions relevées dans différentes pagodes du Sud de l’Inde copiées sur deux volumes manuscrits appartenant à M. A. Gallois-Montbrun</quote>.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f112-f239</locus>: transcriptions of inscriptions in Tamil script.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f240</locus>: title page <quote xml:lang="fr">Inscriptions tamiles 1852</quote></item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f241-f245</locus>: transcriptions of inscriptions in Tamil script.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f246-f266</locus>: translations of inscriptions into French.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f267</locus>: TBC.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f268-f270</locus>: TBC.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f271</locus>: extract from the <title xml:lang="sa">Kāvyaprakāśa</title></item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f272</locus>: TBC.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f273</locus>: title page <quote xml:lang="fr">papiers divers</quote></item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f274</locus>: <foreign xml:lang="sa">yantra</foreign>.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f275</locus>: <foreign xml:lang="sa">yantra</foreign> (one folded folio).</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f276-f277</locus>: syllabary.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f278</locus>: TBC.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f279</locus>: <foreign xml:lang="sa">yantra</foreign>.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f280</locus>: <title xml:lang="ta">Tacamaṇimālai</title></item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f281</locus>: <foreign xml:lang="sa">yantra</foreign> (?) in the form of a lotus (colour painting; folded folio).</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f282-f288</locus>: <foreign xml:lang="sa">yantra</foreign>s with labels.</item>
        <item><locus facs="0">f289</locus>: TBC.</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f290-f291</locus>: <quote>INSCRIPTION BILINGUE DE THUGGA</quote> (printed item; 2 folded folios).</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f292-f293</locus>: <quote>INSCRIPTION BILINGUE DE THUGGA</quote> (printed item, same as preceding; 2 folded folios).</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f294</locus>: title page <quote>Inscriptions sanskrites 1852</quote></item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f295-f296</locus>: transcription in <foreign>devanāgarī</foreign> (in fact one folio folded).</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f297-f325</locus>: Nāgarī/Brāhmī syllabary (versos blank).</item>
    <item><locus facs="0">f326-f329</locus>: translation of 9 inscriptions into French.</item>
      </list>
</p></summary>

						
